BN in revenue on-line. Major initiatives include driving growth through Web, Social and Mobile platforms for Avon Representatives and consumers, driving improved service and efficiency through ERP and providing data and analytics to enable growth strategies.Herlihy joined Avon in March 2008 from the Wrigley Company where he also was CIO. In his 7 years at Wrigley he drove the transformation of Wrigley’s business processes, enabled by a global implementation of SAP. In addition to leading IT, He also served successively as Vice President of Human Resources and Vice President of Supply Chain.Prior to Wrigley, He spent six years at Gillette, ultimately leading Information Technology at its Duracell subsidiary. Earlier in his career, Herlihy was based in the UK, where he worked in manufacturing, business process reengineering and information technology in both the consumer goods and automotive sectors.He holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Industrial Engineering from Dublin Institute of Technology & Trinity College, Dublin, Ireland and he has completed the Executive Program at the University of Michigan, Ross School of Business.He is a board member of The American Red Cross, New York.CIO and VP Supply ChainWrigleyDecember 2000  –  February 2008 (7 years 3 months)VP Supply Chain and Chief Information Officer (CIO) for the Wrigley Company. Responsible for the strategic direction for the global Supply Chain and for all aspects of Information Technology (IT).  As CIO he drove the transformation of the Company’s organization and business processes, enabled by a global implementation of SAP. In 2006 also served as Vice President - Human Resources for the Wrigley company.Director ITGillette1993  –  1998 (5 years)Led IT for the Duracell DivisionIT Manager - UKParker Pen LtdJanuary 1990  –  July 1993 (3 years 7 months)Business AnalystLucas Diesel Systems1988  –  1990 (2 years)OrganizationsRed CrossSkillsIT StrategyStrategyLeadershipCross-functional Team LeadershipSupply Chain 