                Donagh Herlihy
              
                  



Executive Vice President Digital & Chief Information Officer Bloomin' Brands, Inc.




Donagh Herlihy is CIO & SVP, IT & eCommerce at Avon Products Inc. He leads an Information Technology organization of 1500 IT professionals and is responsible for IT strategy and operations globally. He reports to the CEO and is a member of the Executive Committee.
Avon IT provides the business systems supporting Avon’s operations in more than 60 countries. In addition IT is responsible for enabling eCommerce for more than 6.5 million Avon Representatives worldwide. Avon runs the third largest eCommerce platform globally with more than $9BN in revenue on-line. Major initiatives include driving growth through Web, Social and Mobile platforms for Avon Representatives and consumers, driving improved service and efficiency through ERP and providing data and analytics to enable growth strategies.
Herlihy joined Avon in March 2008 from the Wrigley Company where he also was CIO. In his 7 years at Wrigley he drove the transformation of Wrigley’s business processes, enabled by a global implementation of SAP. In addition to leading IT, He also served successively as Vice President of Human Resources and Vice President of Supply Chain.
Prior to Wrigley, He spent six years at Gillette, ultimately leading Information Technology at its Duracell subsidiary. Earlier in his career, Herlihy was based in the UK, where he worked in manufacturing, business process reengineering and information technology in both the consumer goods and automotive sectors.
He holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Industrial Engineering from Dublin Institute of Technology & Trinity College, Dublin, Ireland and he has completed the Executive Program at the University of Michigan, Ross School of Business.
He is a board member of The American Red Cross, New York.






